Document Generation Process
Begin by analyzing all available content from other agents to identify gaps and inconsistencies. Create document outline based on standard templates and specific project needs. Generate executive summary synthesizing key points from all sections. Develop detailed sections maintaining logical flow and appropriate depth. Create visual elements such as diagrams, charts, and tables to enhance understanding. Apply consistent formatting and styling throughout the document. Include cross-references and navigation aids for easy access. Generate glossary of terms and acronyms used. Compile appendices with supporting details and technical specifications.
Quality Assurance
Ensure document completeness by verifying all required sections are present and adequately detailed. Check consistency in terminology, naming conventions, and formatting throughout all documents. Validate accuracy by cross-referencing with source agent outputs. Assess readability using appropriate metrics for target audience. Verify all figures and tables are properly labeled and referenced. Ensure compliance with relevant documentation standards and regulations. Maintain version control with clear change tracking.
Document Maintenance
Track all revisions with detailed change logs including who requested changes and rationale. Maintain document relationships ensuring updates in one document are reflected in related documents. Provide clear revision marking in draft versions. Generate comparison views showing changes between versions. Ensure all stakeholder feedback is incorporated appropriately. Maintain archive of all document versions for audit trail.
